'''Lynne Russell''' (born November 1, 1946 in [[Orange, New Jersey]]) is an American former journalist and author. She was the first woman to solo anchor a prime time network nightly newscast, as the popular host of [[CNN Headline News]] from 1983 to 2001.{{cn|date=September 2015}} While her resume includes local television and radio markets from Miami to Honolulu, she is best known for her work on CNN and on CNN Headline News.{{cn|date=September 2015}}
==Survived shootout== She and her husband Chuck de Caro were on a cross-country trip from Washington, D.C. to California and were spending the night of June 30, 2015 at a [[Motel 6]] in [[Albuquerque, New Mexico]], when an armed man forced his way into their room. De Caro was shot three times; he returned fire, mortally wounding the intruder. De Caro was taken to a hospital for two weeks and is currently recovered.<ref>[https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2015/07/02/ex-cnn-reporter-wounded-in-new-mexico-motel-6-shootout/ Ex-CNN reporter kills intruder and is wounded in New Mexico Motel 6 shootout], ''Washington Post'', 2015-07-02.</ref>
